# Every tracked text file is LF, both in the repository and in the working
# tree, on every platform.
#
# "text=auto" lets Git detect which files are text (versus binary) and
# normalise their line endings to LF when they are committed, so no CRLF can
# enter the repository even if a contributor's editor wrote CRLF on disk.
# "eol=lf" additionally forces LF when files are checked out, so the working
# tree is LF too. Both parts override the per-machine core.autocrlf Git
# setting, so contributors need no special Git configuration.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Treat tracked vendored / minified web assets as opaque bytes; do not normalise.
Source/Modules/Celbridge.DocumentEditors/Editors/CodeEditor/min/** binary
Source/Modules/Celbridge.DocumentEditors/Editors/CodeEditor/markdown-preview/lib/** binary
Source/Modules/Celbridge.DocumentEditors/Editors/Notes/lib/** binary
Source/Workspace/Celbridge.Console/Web/Terminal/lib/** binary
Source/Core/Celbridge.WebHost/Web/bootstrap-icons/** binary

# Explicit binary extensions (Git usually auto-detects these, but be explicit).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ttf binary
*.woff2 binary
*.xlsx binary
*.whl binary
